From ce0aeae2b44c279f241304644c6d5958f1362779 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jack Thomson <jackabt@amazon.com>
Date: Mon, 9 Feb 2026 11:52:46 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 92/94] KVM: x86: Add exitless async page fault notification
 via eventfd

When a VMM handles many userfault APFs (e.g. during snapshot restore),
the KVM_RUN exit/re-entry overhead for each fault becomes significant.

Add an exitless notification path: KVM writes APF details to a shared ring
buffer and signals an eventfd instead of exiting.  The vCPU is auto-halted
and the APF auto-accepted, so the handler can resolve the page and signal
completion via the completion ring + eventfd without any vCPU exits.

Falls back to the normal KVM_EXIT_MEMORY_FAULT path if the notify ring is
full.

The shared page contains two rings (notify and complete) of 32 entries
each, backed by a userspace-pinned page.  Completion is driven by a
workqueue that polls the completion eventfd.

Signed-off-by: Jack Thomson <jackabt@amazon.com>
